      <description>&lt;p&gt;Blowfish provides a feature to group a set of articles together under a &amp;ldquo;series&amp;rdquo;. Placing an article under a series will display the rest of the series articles in each single page and provide a quick way to navigate amongst them. You can see an example of this above.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Create Taxonomy 
    &lt;div id=&#34;create-taxonomy&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#create-taxonomy&#34; aria-label=&#34;Ancora&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first step to enable series is to create the &lt;code&gt;series&lt;/code&gt; taxonomy. For doing this just add the &lt;code&gt;series&lt;/code&gt; taxonomy to your taxonomy list in the &lt;code&gt;config.toml&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
